By Rebecca Phillips 

Termites can cause significant damages to both residential and commercial properties. These invasive insects attack building structures at the foundation or at the wood materials that make up their basic structures. If you own a home or a business, there are a number of reasons why you need the services for termite removal Lyons residents trust.

You should understand that these services are not just for people who are already noticing the signs of termite damage around their properties. Every homeowner must be proactive in preventing infestations of these and other insects if they want their investments to retain their value. Using regular pest management and pest control services is far more cost-effective than treating an infestation after it is already full-blown.

Beyond getting rid of small clusters of insects that are on or around the building, your provider can implement a number of preventative strategies for deterring these bugs from actually congregating on your property. They can suggest tips like getting rid of rotting tree stumps and eliminating or covering any standing or stagnant pools of water. These efforts are designed to make your abode less habitable to termites. If these bugs are not able to easily access the food and water that they need for maintaining robust colonies, they will ultimately move in search of a better area to live and breed.

They eat cellulose or wood and this means that they will ultimately undermine your support beams, walls and other structural elements. After they have managed to actually enter the home, they can even begin feeding on the wood furniture that you own. You will also find wood shavings, termite droppings and other forms of debris that let you know they are present.

Once these insects begin setting up colonies inside, under or around your home, they may begin to expand exponentially. Their breeding practices can give rise to new colonies that branch off and begin causing troubles in other areas of the building. This is how termite infestations quickly spiral out of control.

In addition to considering the potential for structural harm and the negative impact that property damages will have on your home value, you should think about the well-being of the people who live in the structure. These bugs leave behind a lot of debris like feces, carcasses and even wings that can irritate the respiratory system and lower the quality of the indoor air. This can be a huge problem for anyone who is currently dealing with a chronic respiratory issue.

Many homeowners try to treat these problems on their own by purchasing products at local hardware or home stores. Even though there are a number of strong chemicals in these solutions, they may not be effective. It is also best to use a treatment plan that is multi-pronged, rather than simply spraying for bugs alone.

Beyond being less than effective for getting rid of an entire colony of termites, these treatments cannot break breeding cycles in most instances. They are only capable of killing off insects that are fully matured. After any eggs have the chance to hatch and the resulting larvae mature, breeding cycles will begin again and populations will arise once more. This makes it far better to have commercial-grade treatments disbursed by qualified professionals who can also implement elimination and pest management plans that are targeted and multi-dimensional.

posts.title: Úrokové sazby spořicích účtů: Kdy porostou?
posts.text:
Banky 07.11.2017 | 08:33 0 Komentárov 
Dnes jsou tomu 4 roky od zahájení kurzového závazku ČNB. Ten již skončil. Zároveň ČNB již dvakrát zvýšila základní úrokové sazby. Přidaly banky i svým spořícím klientům? 
Česká národní banka (ČNB) stlačila úrokové sazby na historické minimum. A nestačilo pouze snížení základních úrokových sazeb na technickou nulu k 2. listopadu 2012 . Pokračovala dál tiskem peněz s honosným názvem „ kurzový závazek “, který dál plnil banky volnými penězi a tlačil úrokové sazby ještě níže. Kurzovým závazkem odstartovala ČNB tisk peněz ve velkém přesně před 4 lety 7. listopadu 2013. 
Kurzový závazek se stal minulostí usnesením Bankovní rady ČNB 6. března 2017. Peníze v bankách ale zůstaly. A uvolnění kurzu se projevilo u hypoték, kde navíc působily více jiné vlivy – zejména nový zákon o spotřebitelském úvěru a omezení hypoték ze strany ČNB. Více radosti mohlo spořícím klientům přinést navýšení základních úrokových sazeb. Ale nestalo se… Dvojí navýšení sazeb a žádná reakce 
Česká národní banka navýšila své základní sazby po ukončení kurzového závazku již dvakrát. Poprvé 4. srpna 2017 a podruhé od 3. listopadu 2017. Ani jednou na to ale komerční banky nezareagovaly růstem úrokových sazeb na spořicích účtech. 
Celý článok si môžete prečítať na investujeme.cz.

posts.author: BreakingNews.ie
posts.title: Charity warns that Ireland's growing and ageing population faces cancer epidemic
posts.text:
07/11/2017 - 09:02:44 Back to Ireland Home 
The country is facing a "cancer epidemic" with rising numbers of people being diagnosed with the disease, a leading health charity has warned. 
Unless the health system is properly equipped to deal with the increase, the ability to deliver the best outcomes for patients will diminish, the Irish Cancer Society has said. 
Although there is an increase in the number of people being diagnosed with cancer, more sufferers than ever before are winning the battle against the disease, the organisation added. 
According to the National Cancer Registry's annual report more than 40,000 people in Ireland are diagnosed with cancer or a related tumour each year. 
While about 9,000 people are dying from the disease annually, figures from the report show that there are more than 165,000 cancer survivors in Ireland. 
Donal Buggy, head of services and advocacy at the Irish Cancer Society, said the rates of cancer per 100,000 people in Ireland appear to be stabilising. 
He warned however that because of the growing and ageing population, the number of people in Ireland being diagnosed with the disease continues to rise. 
He added: "As such, we are facing into a cancer epidemic. If our health system is not properly equipped to deal with this, our ability to deliver the best outcomes for patients will diminish. 
"It is hugely welcome to see that more people are surviving cancer. 
"This is largely due to better treatments and earlier diagnosis through screening and greater public awareness of symptoms." 
Mr Buggy stressed the importance of a National Cancer Strategy, which includes increasing the proportion of cancers diagnosed at an earlier stage so that more lives can be saved. 
He said the strategy should also offer cancer survivors a treatment summary and care plan to better communicate and co-ordinate survivorship care. 
"This vision requires investment to make it a reality. The Government needs to ensure that resources are frontloaded and made available early in the strategy to ensure its recommendations are fully implemented," he added. 
Mr Buggy also stressed that four out of 10 cancer cases are preventable by making simple lifestyle choices, as outlined in the European Code Against Cancer. 
He has urged everyone to visit the website cancer.ie/europeancode to find out how to reduce their risk.

posts.title: Worst customer relations ever
posts.text:
I booked a simple one way flight for 2 people from Japan to Sth Korea on a Korean company, Busan air through Kiwi.com. I noticed a spelling mistake in my name that I accepted as my fault and tried to contact them to correct it.
Well what an experience in doing nothing that was. I tried online to edit my details. Can't do that but you can edit your passport details or anyone that can hack the system can.
12 days prior to the flight I rang Kiwi.com and I was told to submit an image of my passport to the support section, which by the way the emails keep bouncing back from support.en@kiwi.com, and was told will be the mistake will be corrected in 24 to 48 hours and there may be a fee which I said I was happy to pay.
At that time I also sent a request to add booked baggage for 2, which you cannot do when booking tickets online with this firm.
It took 4 days and 2 requests to get the baggage amended.
The name change request took 12 days, 5 online chats, with 5 promises that it will be corrected within 48 hours and Nothing but Promises.
The last online chat with a "travel consultant" less than 24 hours before the flight, I was informed that Kiwi.com didn't have anyone that spoke Korean on duty and that was part of the problem, and then put the blame on Busan Air for not returning the phone calls about the issue or having English speaking staff.
This is a company that promotes itself as a world wide travel company but cannot speak any other languages. Go figure.
All the time they tell you that you need to print the voucher to present at the counter, and the name on the voucher has to match you passport. I was told to go to the Busan Air counter at the airport in Japan and fix the problem myself. Great customer service.
On arrival at the counter the lovely Korean lady, who spoke good English told me that Busan Air could not change names on tickets purchased through third parties, only the company selling the tickets can do that. She searched the database for my name as per the spelling mistake but could not find it. when she searched for my booking under my correct name, it came up straight away. She could not tell me when the change occurred but it was ther for Kiwi.com to see, and also the printing of the voucher is a load of crap because all you need is your passport.
If you book with this company go ahead, and there are other online companies that can match kiwi.coms prices or even the airlines themselves, but do not any decent customer service if something is not right. It is so easy to for companies to tell you anything when its all done by online chats. 5 times they told me sorry for any inconvenience, but in reality they don't care as long as they have your money which they get upfront.
My advice book with someone else, all online travel companies when nothing goes amiss.

posts.title: West Ham opt for David Moyes as their new manager
posts.text:
07/11/2017 - 09:14:18 Back to Sport Home 
David Moyes has been named as struggling West Ham's new manager. 
The Premier League club have announced the 54-year-old former Everton, Manchester United and Sunderland manager as successor to Slaven Bilic who was sacked on Monday. 
Bilic had been expected to see out the season with the Hammers but he was dismissed by joint-chairmen David Sullivan and David Gold in the wake of the 4-1 home defeat by Liverpool on Saturday. 
The club have not disclosed the length of Moyes' contract. 
Sullivan told the club website: "I would like to welcome David to West Ham United. 
"This is a unique position for David Gold and myself - it is the first time in almost eight years at West Ham United that we have appointed a new manager during the season. 
"We need somebody with experience, knowledge of the Premier League and the players in it, and we believe David is the right man to turn things around and get the best out of the players at the club. 
"He is highly regarded and respected within the game, and will bring fresh ideas, organisation and enthusiasm. 
"He proved with Everton that he has great qualities and we feel that West Ham United is a club that will give David the platform to display those qualities again." 
Moyes has been out of management since he resigned from Sunderland at the end of last season, having failed to save them from relegation. 
His appointment has been met with scepticism by some Hammers fans following his disappointing spells with United and the Black Cats, as well as an underwhelming stint in Spain with Real Sociedad. 
Nevertheless, Sullivan and Gold are backing Moyes to help shore up a leaky defence as well as getting the best out of big-money summer signings Marko Arnautovic and Javier Hernandez. 
Club-record capture Arnautovic has been such a disappointment he was booed off during the recent home defeat by Brighton. 
Despite the poor start to the season, Sullivan and Gold wanted Bilic to see out the three-year contract he signed in June 2015. 
But the manner of their capitulation on Saturday evening prompted them to dispense with the Croatian's services, which they say they did with "heavy hearts". 
Less than 24 later Moyes was meeting his new players for the first time at the club's Rush Green training ground. His first game in charge will be at Watford a week on Sunday. 
"I'm really looking forward to meeting the supporters and being in the stadium with them," Moyes said in a first interview published on the club's Twitter feed. 
"I'm looking forward to seeing them get right behind the team, and my team also. We need the support, we need everybody with us. 
"It's a big job we have in hand now but I'm sure with everybody together we can get the right results between now and the end of the season."

Evin içerisinde AFAD ve sağlık ekiplerince altına branda serilen Duva, özel asansörlü sedye ile saatler süren çalışmaların ardından pencereden çıkarıldı. thread.title_full: Man Who Exchanged Fire With Texas Shooter: 'I Was Scared To Death'

posts.author: Scott Neuman
posts.title: Man Who Exchanged Fire With Texas Shooter: 'I Was Scared To Death'
posts.text:
By Scott Neuman • 27 minutes ago Stephen Willeford, right and Johnnie Langendorff, left, attend a vigil for the victims of the First Baptist Church shooting on Monday, in Sutherland Springs, Texas. Willeford shot suspect Devin Patrick Kelley, and Langendorff drove the truck while chasing Kelley. David J. Phillip / AP 
The Sutherland Springs, Texas, resident who exchanged gunfire with the suspect in Sunday's mass shooting at a church insists he is not a hero, saying the he was "scared to death" during the encounter. 
"I think my God, my Lord protected me and gave me the skills to do what needed to be done," Stephen Willeford, a former National Rifle Association instructor, tells KHBS/KHOG television in Arkansas. 
Willeford says his daughter alerted him to what sounded like shots being fired at the nearby First Baptist Church. That's when he said he got his rifle out of his safe. 
"I kept hearing the shots, one after another, very rapid shots — just 'pop pop pop pop' and I knew every one of those shots represented someone, that it was aimed at someone, that they weren't just random shots," Willeford said. 
"I was scared to death, I was," a visibly shaken Willeford told the television station. "I was scared for me. I was scared for every one of them and I was scared for my own family that lived less than a block away." 
Willeford said he loaded a magazine in his rifle and ran across the street without even taking the time to put on his shoes. 
When he saw the suspect, identified by police as Devin Patrick Kelley, the two exchanged gunfire. 
"He saw me and I saw him," Willeford said. "I was standing behind a pickup truck for cover." 
"I know I hit him," Willeford said. "He got into his vehicle, and he fired another couple rounds through his side window. When the window dropped, I fired another round at him again." 
Kelley was reportedly wearing tactical gear and wielding a variant of the AR-15 assault rifle. 
When the gunman sped away, Willeford saw a pickup truck and quickly explained the situation to the driver, later identified as Johnnie Langendorff, and the two set off on a high-speed chase to run down the attacker. 
Langendorff told KSAT that Willeford "came to my vehicle in distress with his weapon" and said "'we need to pursue him. He just shot up the church.' " 
Langendorff said he and the other man pursued the shooter at high speed before he appeared to lose control and go off the road. "The other gentleman jumped out and had his rifle on him and he didn't move after that," Langendorff told the TV station. 
Kelley's vehicle, a truck, hit a road sign and flip before landing in a ditch, KHBS/KHOG says. Willeford says he put his rifle on the top of the truck and yelled to the suspect "get out of the truck, get out of the truck," but never saw any movement until law enforcement arrived a few minutes later. 
Freeman Martin, regional director of the state's Department of Public Safety, said the cause of Kelley's death had not been determined. "However, investigators found evidence at the scene that indicates the subject may have died from a self-inflicted gunshot wound." Copyright 2017 NPR. To see more, visit http://www.npr.org/. posts.text: 凯利为何选择到第一浸信会教堂开枪，作案动机仍未明了。 美国 有线电视新闻网（CNN）6日报导，凯利疑似与丈母娘有纠纷，直到枪击案发生之前，还发送语带恐吓的简讯给岳母。德州公共安全局首长马丁（Freeman Martin）对媒体表示，根据调查，凯利曾经对丈母娘表达高度不满，而丈母娘是第一浸信会教堂成员，平常会到教堂作礼拜，但案发当天她并没有在教堂里。不过，她的母亲怀特（Lula White）则不幸在这起重大枪击案中丧生。 德州枪击案26死，枪手似乎不只一次重新装弹 。 （Erich Schlegel/Getty Images） 警方：凶嫌死于自杀 该案案发于当地时间周日（11月5日）上午11点20分左右，居住在德州新布朗费尔斯市（New Braunfels）的26岁白人青年德文．凯利（Devin Patrick Kelley），身着全套战术装备和防弹背心，手持鲁格AR突击步枪（Ruger AR assault type rifle），出现在德州小镇萨瑟兰泉（Sutherland Springs）的教堂内，该教堂位于他居住地以南30多英里。凯利进门后立即向正在做礼拜的民众们开火，酿成至少26死20伤的惨剧，受害者年龄最大77岁，最小才18个月。枪击发生后，2名当地居民奋勇的抢夺凯利的武器，凯利扔下武器，开车逃离，2名平民英雄也一起驱车追赶。双方追逐10到12分钟后，凯利的车失去控制，撞毁在路边。警方到达时发现凯利死在车里，并在他的车中发现武器装备。威尔森郡（Wilson County）警长塔基特（Joe Tackitt）6日早上告诉美国哥伦比亚广播公司新闻网（CBS News），他相信就在那时（车失去控制时）嫌犯开枪自杀。美国空军发言人证实，凯利2009年加入美国空军，2012年因殴打妻儿，在军事法庭受审，被判入狱12个月，2014年被开除。（记者李红报导/责任编辑：程以仁）
